cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NI 

The paper deals with the problem of adversarial attacks on deep neural networks used for malware classification. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as well as machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the use of the DREBIN Android malware dataset suggests a potential connection to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
